  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering generally refers to financial transactions designed to conceal the origins of illegally obtained money. Key legal definitions typically involve three main stages:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Conducting complex financial transactions to obscure the money's source\n3. Integration: Reintroducing the \"cleaned\" money into legitimate economic channels\n\nSpecific legal definitions vary by jurisdiction, but most include:\n- Knowingly processing proceeds from criminal activities\n- Attempting to disguise the source of illegally obtained funds\n- Transferring or converting property to conceal its illegal origin\n- Participating in financial transactions to hide criminal proceeds\n\nPrecise definitions and penalties differ between countries' legal systems.",
